org.semanticweb.owlapi.model

Interface MIMETypeAware

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    OWLDocumentFormatFactory, OWLParserFactory
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DLSyntaxDocumentFormatFactory, DLSyntaxHTMLDocumentFormatFactory, DLSyntaxOWLParserFactory, FunctionalSyntaxDocumentFormatFactory, KRSS2DocumentFormatFactory, KRSS2OWLParserFactory, KRSSDocumentFormatFactory, KRSSOWLParserFactory, LabelFunctionalDocumentFormatFactory, LatexAxiomsListDocumentFormatFactory, LatexDocumentFormatFactory, ManchesterOWLSyntaxOntologyParserFactory, ManchesterSyntaxDocumentFormatFactory, OBODocumentFormatFactory, OBOFormatOWLAPIParserFactory, OWLDocumentFormatFactoryImpl, OWLFunctionalSyntaxOWLParserFactory, OWLParserFactoryImpl, OWLXMLDocumentFormatFactory, OWLXMLParserFactory, RDFXMLDocumentFormatFactory, RDFXMLParserFactory, TurtleDocumentFormatFactory, TurtleOntologyParserFactory

    public interface MIMETypeAware
    Interface for MIME type aware objects. These can be instances of format, parser or storer factories. Formats can use annotations for the same purpose, but generic factories cannot use type annotations to change behaviour.
    Since:
    4.0.0
    Author:
    ignazio

      • getDefaultMIMEType

        @Nullable
String getDefaultMIMEType()
        Returns the default MIME Type for the OWLDocumentFormat that this class is a factory for.
        Returns:
        The default MIME Type for the OWLDocumentFormat that this class is a factory for or null if no MIME Types are specified.

      • getMIMETypes

        default List<String> getMIMETypes()
        Returns a sorted list of MIME types for the OWLDocumentFormat that this class is a factory for. If this list is not empty, the first element in the returned list must be the default MIME type.
        Returns:
        A list of strings containing the known MIME types for this format.

      • handlesMimeType

        default boolean handlesMimeType(String mimeType)
        Determines whether either getDefaultMIMEType() equals the given mime type or getMIMETypes() contains the given mime type.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        True if the given MIME type matches this format.
